 </code><br>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td class="number">4</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code>Section 5. </code><code>The Higher Education Student Assistance Act is </code></td></tr><tr><td class="number">5</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>amended  by adding Section 65.105 as follows:</code><br>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td class="number">6</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code>(110 ILCS 947/65.105 new)</code></td></tr><tr><td class="number">7</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><u><code>Sec. 65.105. </code></u><u><code>Adult vocational community college </code></u></td></tr><tr><td class="number">8</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><u><code>scholarship.</code></u></td></tr><tr><td class="number">9</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><u><code>(a) The Commission shall, subject to appropriation, </code></u></td></tr><tr><td class="number">10</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><u><code>establish and administer an adult vocational community college </code></u></td></tr><tr><td class="number">11</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><u><code>scholarship program.</code></u><code> </code></td></tr><tr><td class="number">12</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><u><code>(b) Beginning with the 2020-2021 academic year, the </code></u></td></tr><tr><td class="number">13</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><u><code>Commission shall, each year, receive and consider applications </code></u></td></tr><tr><td class="number">14</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><u><code>for scholarships under this Section. An applicant is eligible </code></u></td></tr><tr><td class="number">15</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><u><code>for a scholarship under this Section if the Commission finds </code></u></td></tr><tr><td 